We can use Cp method to determine which variance should be considered into model. When the Cp for select model is close to p, the select model is appropriate one. We can also use stepwise method to choose best model.

Base= lm(y.911~1, data=data.911)
Retailer<- lm(data.911$proficiency~ ., data = data.911)
step(Base,scope=list(upper=Retailer,lower=~1),direction="both",trace=FALSE)

pred1= fitted.values(fit.1010)
v=c(16,22,43,48,10,32,38,40)

for(i in v ){
  newdata.1010= data.1010[-i,]
  fit2.1010=lm(y.1010~x1.1010+x2.1010+x3.1010, data = newdata.1010)
  pred2=predict(fit2.1010,data.frame(x1.1010=data.1010[,2],x2.1010=data.1010[,3],x3.1010=data.1010[,4]))
  m=mean(abs((pred2-pred1)/pred1*100))
  print(c(i,m))
}
